remely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Margaret Bowman was born about 1191, in England, United Kingdom. She married Jacob Bellinger before 1217, in England. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"about 1191–":"umbes 1191–Surnud","1188–Male":"1188–Surnud","1217–1297":"1217–1297","1191–Female":"1191–Surnud","1217":"1217","about 1217":"umbes 1217","about 1191":"umbes 1191","1188":"1188","1297":"1297","before 1217":"enne 1217","1191":"1191","Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"England","England, United Kingdom":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1191–":"noin 1191–Kuollut","1188–Male":"1188–Kuollut","1217–1297":"1217–1297","1191–Female":"1191–Kuollut","1217":"1217","about 1217":"noin 1217","about 1191":"noin 1191","1188":"1188","1297":"1297","before 1217":"ennen vuotta 1217","1191":"1191","Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"England","England, United Kingdom":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1191–":"environ 1191–Décédée","1188–Male":"1188–Décédé","1217–1297":"1217–1297","1191–Female":"1191–Décédée","1217":"1217","about 1217":"environ 1217","about 1191":"environ 1191","1188":"1188","1297":"1297","before 1217":"avant 1217","1191":"1191","Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","England":"Angleterre","England, United Kingdom":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Margaret Bowman est née environ 1191, à Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a épousé Jacob Bellinger avant 1217, à Angleterre. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fille."},"de":{"about 1191–":"um 1191–Verstorben","1188–Male":"1188–Verstorben","1217–1297":"1217–1297","1191–Female":"1191–Verstorben","1217":"1217","about 1217":"um 1217","about 1191":"um 1191","1188":"1188","1297":"1297","before 1217":"vor 1217","1191":"1191","Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, England, United K